ge of the Holy Cross, Worcester, Massachusetts, where he served as director of Peace and Conflict Studies and editor-in-chief of Diotima: A Philosophical Review. His publications include Anamorphosis: Kant on Knowledge and Ignorance (1997), Between Truth and Illusion: Kant at the Crossroads of Modernity (2002), Essays by Lewis White Beck: Fifty Years as a Philosopher (1998), and Kant's Legacy: Essays in Honor of Lewis White Beck (2001).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEthics, Moderny20th century. 0aGood and evil. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aart.  acorrespondence.  aessays.  aevil.  ahistory.  ahuman lives.  ainterviews.  aliterary criticism.  anightmarish memories.  aopinions.  aphilosophy.  apolitical science.  apsychology.  aquestions.  areligious studies.  aresponses.  astories.  astruggle.  atheology.  atreatises.  atwentieth century.1 aAnderson-Gold, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArendt, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBailie, Gil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerrigan S.J., Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerrigan, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamus, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCicovacki, Predrag, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCicovacki, Predrag, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCollins, John P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDel Prete, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEinstein, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular